int main(){
    printf("Class objects are templates that define attributes and methods. Instance objects are concrete objects created from a class; they have their own attribute values but share the class's methods. When an attribute is accessed on an instance, the lookup order is: instance namespace, then the class, then base classes following the method resolution order (MRO).
");
    return 0;
}

